body_html:
Thank you for letting me know Eugene. I didn't read that previous message and didn't realize --update_goldens=True doesn't work either. I thought only error printing is messed up.

Also, I am still working on fixing the error message. But for now I patched this change and ran api_compatibility_test. The change I see is:

member_method {
    name: "stateless_random_uniform_int"
    argspec: "args=[\'shape\', \'seed\', \'minval\', \'maxval\', \'name\'], varargs=None, keywords=None, defaults=[\'None\'], "
}

This is added right before "stop_gradient" member_method here:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/tools/api/golden/v1/tensorflow.pbtxt#L2059

The same change also needs to be made to tensorflow/tools/api/golden/v2/tensorflow.pbtxt file.

@girving does api_compatibility_test pass for you locally or does it fail for you but doesn't update the goldens?
body:
Thank you for letting me know Eugene. I didn't read that previous message and didn't realize --update_goldens=True doesn't work either. I thought only error printing is messed up.

Also, I am still working on fixing the error message. But for now I patched this change and ran api_compatibility_test. The change I see is:
```
member_method {
    name: "stateless_random_uniform_int"
    argspec: "args=[\'shape\', \'seed\', \'minval\', \'maxval\', \'name\'], varargs=None, keywords=None, defaults=[\'None\'], "
}
```
This is added right before "stop_gradient" member_method here:
https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/tools/api/golden/v1/tensorflow.pbtxt#L2059

The same change also needs to be made to tensorflow/tools/api/golden/v2/tensorflow.pbtxt file.

@girving does api_compatibility_test pass for you locally or does it fail for you but doesn't update the goldens?
